descript.abstract: This line data layer represents roads for Waupaca County, Wisconsin in 2014. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Waupaca_Roads_2014.gdb. [This data represents the Waupaca County transportation network. A single line is used to represent the center of a road. All roads are geocoded with a address range.]
descript.purpose: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [These files are maintained primarily for use as base data for digital mapping, county addressing activities, and right of way designations. In 2006 the Sheriff's Department began using road centerline data as there base information layer for Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) System. The CAD system has a mapping component that can geocode addresses based on road centerline range data. The mapping componet of the CAD system can now display locations of E911 cellular calls.]
